The paper deals with the wiretap channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The focus is on the multiple access aspect of the channel, which involves multiple users transmitting simultaneously, making it relevant to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of achievable schemes, which is a common approach in multimedia (cs.MM) and networking (cs.NI) research.
